{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"My work is about the behaviors that we all engage in unconsciously,"},{"time":5000,"text":"on a collective level."},{"time":7000,"text":"And what I mean by that, it's the behaviors"},{"time":9000,"text":"that we're in denial about,"},{"time":10000,"text":"and the ones that operate below the surface of our daily awareness."},{"time":17000,"text":"And as individuals, we all do these things, all the time, everyday."},{"time":20000,"text":"It's like when you're mean to your wife"},{"time":23000,"text":"because you're mad at somebody else."},{"time":25000,"text":"Or when you drink a little too much at a party, just out of anxiety."},{"time":28000,"text":"Or when you overeat because your feelings are hurt, or whatever."},{"time":34000,"text":"And when we do these kind of things,"},{"time":36000,"text":"when 300 million people do unconscious behaviors,"},{"time":40000,"text":"then it can add up to a catastrophic consequence"},{"time":43000,"text":"that nobody wants, and no one intended."},{"time":45000,"text":"And that's what I look at with my photographic work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":48000,"text":"This is an image I just recently completed, that is --"},{"time":52000,"text":"when you stand back at a distance,"},{"time":53000,"text":"it looks like some kind of neo-Gothic, cartoon image"},{"time":56000,"text":"of a factory spewing out pollution."},{"time":59000,"text":"And as you get a little bit closer,"},{"time":62000,"text":"it starts looking like lots of pipes, like maybe a chemical plant,"},{"time":66000,"text":"or a refinery, or maybe a hellish freeway interchange."},{"time":70000,"text":"And as you get all the way up close,"},{"time":71000,"text":"you realize that it's actually made of lots and lots of plastic cups."},{"time":76000,"text":"And in fact, this is one million plastic cups,"},{"time":78000,"text":"which is the number of plastic cups that are used on airline flights"},{"time":83000,"text":"in the United States every six hours."},{"time":84000,"text":"We use four million cups a day on airline flights,"},{"time":89000,"text":"and virtually none of them are reused or recycled."},{"time":91000,"text":"They just don't do that in that industry."}]},{"cues":[{"time":94000,"text":"Now, that number is dwarfed"},{"time":96000,"text":"by the number of paper cups we use every day,"},{"time":99000,"text":"and that is 40 million cups a day for hot beverages,"},{"time":102000,"text":"most of which is coffee."},{"time":103000,"text":"I couldn't fit 40 million cups on a canvas,"},{"time":106000,"text":"but I was able to put 410,000. That's what 410,000 cups looks like."},{"time":111000,"text":"That's 15 minutes of our cup consumption."},{"time":112000,"text":"And if you could actually stack up that many cups in real life,"},{"time":116000,"text":"that's the size it would be."},{"time":117000,"text":"And there's an hour's worth of our cups."},{"time":120000,"text":"And there's a day's worth of our cups."},{"time":121000,"text":"You can still see the little people way down there."},{"time":123000,"text":"That's as high as a 42-story building,"},{"time":125000,"text":"and I put the Statue of Liberty in there as a scale reference."}]},{"cues":[{"time":131000,"text":"Speaking of justice, there's another phenomenon going on in our culture"},{"time":134000,"text":"that I find deeply troubling, and that is that America, right now,"},{"time":137000,"text":"has the largest percentage of its population in prison"},{"time":140000,"text":"of any country on Earth."},{"time":143000,"text":"One out of four people, one out of four humans in prison"},{"time":146000,"text":"are Americans, imprisoned in our country."},{"time":151000,"text":"And I wanted to show the number."},{"time":152000,"text":"The number is 2.3 million Americans were incarcerated in 2005."},{"time":156000,"text":"And that's gone up since then, but we don't have the numbers yet."},{"time":158000,"text":"So, I wanted to show 2.3 million prison uniforms,"},{"time":162000,"text":"and in the actual print of this piece,"},{"time":165000,"text":"each uniform is the size of a nickel on its edge."},{"time":168000,"text":"They're tiny. They're barely visible as a piece of material,"},{"time":171000,"text":"and to show 2.3 million of them required a canvas"},{"time":175000,"text":"that was larger than any printer in the world would print."},{"time":177000,"text":"And so I had to divide it up into multiple panels"},{"time":179000,"text":"that are 10 feet tall by 25 feet wide."},{"time":181000,"text":"This is that piece installed in a gallery in New York --"},{"time":186000,"text":"those are my parents looking at the piece."},{"time":188000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":191000,"text":"Every time I look at this piece,"},{"time":192000,"text":"I always wonder if my mom's whispering to my dad,"},{"time":194000,"text":"\"He finally folded his laundry.\""},{"time":196000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":199000,"text":"I want to show you some pieces now that are about addiction."},{"time":201000,"text":"And this particular one is about cigarette addiction."},{"time":205000,"text":"I wanted to make a piece that shows the actual number of Americans"},{"time":208000,"text":"who die from cigarette smoking."},{"time":210000,"text":"More than 400,000 people die in the United States every year"},{"time":213000,"text":"from smoking cigarettes."},{"time":215000,"text":"And so, this piece is made up of lots and lots of boxes of cigarettes."},{"time":219000,"text":"And, as you slowly step back,"},{"time":220000,"text":"you see that it's a painting by Van Gogh, called \"Skull with Cigarette.\""},{"time":224000,"text":"It's a strange thing to think about, that on 9/11,"},{"time":228000,"text":"when that tragedy happened, 3,000 Americans died."},{"time":230000,"text":"And do you remember the response?"},{"time":233000,"text":"It reverberated around the world,"},{"time":235000,"text":"and will continue to reverberate through time."},{"time":238000,"text":"It will be something that we talk about in 100 years."},{"time":241000,"text":"And yet on that same day, 1,100 Americans died from smoking."},{"time":246000,"text":"And the day after that, another 1,100 Americans died from smoking."},{"time":249000,"text":"And every single day since then, 1,100 Americans have died."},{"time":253000,"text":"And today, 1,100 Americans are dying from cigarette smoking."},{"time":255000,"text":"And we aren't talking about it -- we dismiss it."},{"time":260000,"text":"The tobacco lobby, it's too strong."},{"time":262000,"text":"We just dismiss it out of our consciousness."},{"time":266000,"text":"And knowing what we know about the destructive power of cigarettes,"},{"time":272000,"text":"we continue to allow our children, our sons and daughters,"},{"time":276000,"text":"to be in the presence of the influences that start them smoking."},{"time":279000,"text":"And this is what the next piece is about."}]},{"cues":[{"time":282000,"text":"This is just lots and lots of cigarettes: 65,000 cigarettes,"},{"time":285000,"text":"which is equal to the number of teenagers"},{"time":288000,"text":"who will start smoking this month, and every month in the U.S."},{"time":291000,"text":"More than 700,000 children in the United States aged 18 and under"},{"time":295000,"text":"begin smoking every year."}]},{"cues":[{"time":297000,"text":"One more strange epidemic in the United States"},{"time":303000,"text":"that I want to acquaint you with"},{"time":305000,"text":"is this phenomenon of abuse and misuse of prescription drugs."},{"time":311000,"text":"This is an image I've made out of lots and lots of Vicodin."},{"time":315000,"text":"Well, actually, I only had one Vicodin"},{"time":317000,"text":"that I scanned lots and lots of times."},{"time":319000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":320000,"text":"And so, as you stand back, you see 213,000 Vicodin pills,"},{"time":323000,"text":"which is the number of hospital emergency room visits"},{"time":327000,"text":"yearly in the United States,"},{"time":328000,"text":"attributable to abuse and misuse of prescription painkillers"},{"time":333000,"text":"and anti-anxiety medications."},{"time":334000,"text":"One-third of all drug overdoses in the U.S. --"},{"time":338000,"text":"and that includes cocaine, heroin, alcohol, everything --"},{"time":341000,"text":"one-third of drug overdoses are prescription medications."},{"time":346000,"text":"A strange phenomenon."}]},{"cues":[{"time":347000,"text":"This is a piece that I just recently completed"},{"time":351000,"text":"about another tragic phenomenon. And that is the phenomenon,"},{"time":354000,"text":"this growing obsession we have with breast augmentation surgery."},{"time":360000,"text":"384,000 women, American women, last year"},{"time":364000,"text":"went in for elective breast augmentation surgery."},{"time":369000,"text":"It's rapidly becoming the most popular high school graduation gift,"},{"time":373000,"text":"given to young girls who are about to go off to college."},{"time":379000,"text":"So, I made this image out of Barbie dolls,"},{"time":382000,"text":"and so, as you stand back you see this kind of floral pattern,"},{"time":387000,"text":"and as you get all the way back, you see 32,000 Barbie dolls,"},{"time":391000,"text":"which represents the number of breast augmentation surgeries"},{"time":394000,"text":"that are performed in the U.S. each month."},{"time":396000,"text":"The vast majority of those are on women under the age of 21."},{"time":402000,"text":"And strangely enough, the only plastic surgery"},{"time":404000,"text":"that is more popular than breast augmentation is liposuction,"},{"time":408000,"text":"and most of that is being done by men."}]},{"cues":[{"time":410000,"text":"Now, I want to emphasize that these are just examples."},{"time":414000,"text":"I'm not holding these out as being the biggest issues."},{"time":417000,"text":"They're just examples."},{"time":420000,"text":"And the reason that I do this, it's because I have this fear"},{"time":424000,"text":"that we aren't feeling enough as a culture right now."},{"time":428000,"text":"There's this kind of anesthesia in America at the moment."},{"time":431000,"text":"We've lost our sense of outrage, our anger and our grief"},{"time":439000,"text":"about what's going on in our culture right now,"},{"time":441000,"text":"what's going on in our country,"},{"time":442000,"text":"the atrocities that are being committed in our names around the world."},{"time":444000,"text":"They've gone missing; these feelings have gone missing."},{"time":448000,"text":"Our cultural joy, our national joy is nowhere to be seen."},{"time":451000,"text":"And one of the causes of this, I think,"},{"time":455000,"text":"is that as each of us attempts to build this new kind of worldview,"},{"time":459000,"text":"this holoptical worldview, this holographic image"},{"time":463000,"text":"that we're all trying to create in our mind"},{"time":465000,"text":"of the interconnection of things: the environmental footprints"},{"time":468000,"text":"1,000 miles away of the things that we buy;"},{"time":471000,"text":"the social consequences 10,000 miles away"},{"time":474000,"text":"of the daily decisions that we make as consumers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":477000,"text":"As we try to build this view,"},{"time":479000,"text":"and try to educate ourselves about the enormity of our culture,"},{"time":482000,"text":"the information that we have to work with is these gigantic numbers:"},{"time":488000,"text":"numbers in the millions, in the hundreds of millions,"},{"time":491000,"text":"in the billions and now in the trillions."},{"time":494000,"text":"Bush's new budget is in the trillions, and these are numbers"},{"time":496000,"text":"that our brain just doesn't have the ability to comprehend."},{"time":500000,"text":"We can't make meaning out of these enormous statistics."},{"time":504000,"text":"And so that's what I'm trying to do with my work,"},{"time":508000,"text":"is to take these numbers, these statistics"},{"time":509000,"text":"from the raw language of data, and to translate them"},{"time":514000,"text":"into a more universal visual language, that can be felt."},{"time":517000,"text":"Because my belief is, if we can feel these issues,"},{"time":521000,"text":"if we can feel these things more deeply,"},{"time":523000,"text":"then they'll matter to us more than they do now."},{"time":528000,"text":"And if we can find that,"},{"time":529000,"text":"then we'll be able to find, within each one of us,"},{"time":534000,"text":"what it is that we need to find to face the big question,"},{"time":537000,"text":"which is: how do we change?"},{"time":540000,"text":"That, to me, is the big question that we face as a people right now:"},{"time":545000,"text":"how do we change? How do we change as a culture,"},{"time":549000,"text":"and how do we each individually take responsibility"},{"time":553000,"text":"for the one piece of the solution that we are in charge of,"},{"time":557000,"text":"and that is our own behavior?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":558000,"text":"My belief is that you don't have to make yourself bad"},{"time":568000,"text":"to look at these issues."},{"time":570000,"text":"I'm not pointing the finger at America in a blaming way."},{"time":574000,"text":"I'm simply saying, this is who we are right now."},{"time":576000,"text":"And if there are things that we see"},{"time":578000,"text":"that we don't like about our culture,"},{"time":579000,"text":"then we have a choice."},{"time":590000,"text":"The degree of integrity that each of us can bring to the surface,"},{"time":595000,"text":"to bring to this question, the depth of character that we can summon,"},{"time":602000,"text":"as we show up for the question of how do we change --"},{"time":605000,"text":"it's already defining us as individuals and as a nation,"},{"time":613000,"text":"and it will continue to do that, on into the future."},{"time":616000,"text":"And it will profoundly affect the well-being, the quality of life"},{"time":623000,"text":"of the billions of people"},{"time":624000,"text":"who are going to inherit the results of our decisions."},{"time":633000,"text":"I'm not speaking abstractly about this,"},{"time":634000,"text":"I'm speaking -- this is who we are in this room,"},{"time":644000,"text":"right now, in this moment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":646000,"text":"Thank you and good afternoon."},{"time":651000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}